Provides a resource to create a user in an
[Okta auth backend within Vault](https://www.vaultproject.io/docs/auth/okta.html).


{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage

{{< chooser language "typescript,python,go,csharp" / >}}

{{% example csharp %}}
```csharp
using Pulumi;
using Vault = Pulumi.Vault;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var example = new Vault.Okta.AuthBackend("example", new Vault.Okta.AuthBackendArgs
        {
            Organization = "dummy",
            Path = "user_okta",
        });
        var foo = new Vault.Okta.AuthBackendUser("foo", new Vault.Okta.AuthBackendUserArgs
        {
            Groups = 
            {
                "one",
                "two",
            },
            Path = example.Path,
            Username = "foo",
        });
    }

}
```

{{% /example %}}

{{% example go %}}
```go
package main

import (
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi-vault/sdk/v3/go/vault/okta"
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi/sdk/v2/go/pulumi"
)

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		example, err := okta.NewAuthBackend(ctx, "example", &okta.AuthBackendArgs{
			Organization: pulumi.String("dummy"),
			Path:         pulumi.String("user_okta"),
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		_, err = okta.NewAuthBackendUser(ctx, "foo", &okta.AuthBackendUserArgs{
			Groups: pulumi.StringArray{
				pulumi.String("one"),
				pulumi.String("two"),
			},
			Path:     example.Path,
			Username: pulumi.String("foo"),
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}
```
